          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Special Envoy for Refugees Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the President to appoint a Special Envoy for Refugees whose duties shall include (1) representing the United States in diplomacy related to global displacement, migration, refugees, asylum-seekers, and internally displaced and stateless individuals; and (2) leading interagency coordination to oversee research related to the global refugee crisis and the U.S. refugee program.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-02-06T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
